docs.abstract: Governments need Big Tech now more than ever.
docs.snippet: Governments need Big Tech now more than ever.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last month, as the coronavirus started to spread here in the United States, I wrote about a smallish online conferencing company, Zoom Video Communications, saying that we might want to pay attention to it because it makes working from home easier. Well, with the escalating crisis, Zoom is now worth more than four airlines combined — United, Delta, American and JetBlue — with a market cap of just above $44 billion.

headline.main: Will Our Most Important Industry Survive the Coronavirus?
